Lee, recently named Houston Baptist‚Äôs male athlete of the year, led his team in scoring and rebounding and was sixth in the nation in steals per game, school officials said.

Darius always said he wanted be on TV. He got his wish. But in a wrong and bad way,‚Äù his father, Eric Lee, 50, said Monday. ‚ÄúHe didn‚Äôt deserve this.‚Äù Lee fell in love with basketball at a young age, surprising his youth coach, who noticed that he was a ‚Äúchubby kid‚Äù at age 10, his father recalled.‚ÄúHe said to his coach, ‚ÄòI want to play basketball‚Äô, he said . ‚ÄúThe coach looked at him and said‚Äö ‚ÄòYou?‚Äô‚Äù

"He only cared about basketball,‚Äù said Lee‚Äôs sister Tiara. ‚ÄúHe decided to stay outside one day and this happened . . . These are innocent kids that‚Äôs in school, playing basketball.‚Äù

Lee had NBA dreams, his father said. ‚ÄúHe wanted to be a New York Knick. He was a New York native. And he was on his way. He had a full ride in school full scholarship. The school paid for him to come back and forth,‚Äù Eric Lee said.‚ÄúThe next I know he was at St. Mark‚Äôs with a full scholarship,‚Äù he said, referring to the parochial elementary school St. Mark‚Äôs the Evangelist across the street from his son‚Äôs home on W 138 St. When they spoke Sunday, Lee asked his dad what he wanted for Father‚Äôs Day. ‚ÄúI said, ‚ÄòI want a 2022 white Range Rover, red seats," Eric Lee said. ‚ÄúHe said to me, ‚ÄòI got you.'"

The former player at St. Raymond‚Äôs High School in the Bronx does not appear to have been the intended target, police said.

Lee never cursed, never drank, never hung out on the streets and stayed out of trouble, his father said. ‚ÄúMy brother‚Äôs gone,‚Äù his devastated sister said. ‚ÄúGreat kid. He‚Äôs gone, for no reason.‚Äù

It wasn‚Äôt yet clear what prompted the shooting, which broke out about 12:40 a.m. but police said it involved rival groups shooting at each other in the crowd. One handgun was recovered at the scene.

‚ÄúThey just went to a cookout to listen to music,‚Äù Lee‚Äôs cousin Dee Cook said. ‚ÄúThey just kids, want to enjoy themselves for the summer. A lot of innocent people got hit. They just shooting wild. They don‚Äôt care who they shooting.‚Äù
